      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Limestone having a light gray color, occurring widely throughout Great Britain and Ireland, in deposits dating to the Dinantian Epoch of the Carboniferous Period, from about 345 to 280 million years ago.</Note_Text>
